  "text": "Aplysia californica from the University of Miami National Resource for Aplysia reared from egg masses of wild-caught animals were used in these experiments. Animals from each hatchery-reared cohort were from a single egg mass and thus represent either full or half siblings. For selected experiments, wild-caught adults of indeterminate age but that were sexually mature were used. Animals were fed an ad-libitum diet consisting of Gracilaria ferox and Agardhiella subulata and reared as described previously [CITATION_1] . Four hatcheryreared animals of different weights were assigned to each cage to allow for identification of individual animals by monthly weight measurements. Sexual maturity for a cohort of animals was designated as the day the first egg mass was laid.",
